places.name: Bridgewater
places.desc: Great views of Adelaide bound trains in autumn with the falling leaves

places.name: Dry Creek Turntable
places.desc: Where Locomotives and Rollingstock are Turned as required.

places.name: Mobil Birkenhead
places.desc: Mobil fuel depot, serviced by Aurizon shunts two to three times a week with fuel sent to Alice Springs via AD1/DA2 services.

places.name: Viterra Port Adelaide
places.desc: A small number of South Australian Grain Trains unload here. Formerly where broad gauge SA grain trains unloaded.

places.name: Glengowrie Tram Depot
places.desc: Home base for the Torrens Connect network of Standard Gauge Trams.

places.name: Penfield, Virginia
places.desc: Incredible views off the banks of the bridge for trains going in both directions, also a good spot to look into SCT's yard.

places.name: BlueScope Lysaght Siding, Wingfield.
places.desc: 1160S/1161S SCT Steel Transfers unload and load here.

places.name: Millswood
places.desc: Really good view for trains coming from Melbourne and a slight curve for trains coming from Adelaide, good for photography. Photos work best here when taken in the morning.

places.name: Mt Barker Jct. (MBJ).
places.desc:
Location: 50.0km by Rail from Mile End.
Length: 1550m.

places.name: Motive Power Centre (Dry Creek).
places.desc: Aurizon's Locomotive Maintenance and Provisioning Facility for the Bulk Central Division.

places.name: Hawker Street
places.desc: Great views of trains in either directions, parking and shade/seats there too

places.name: Korunye
places.desc: Great viewing of trains going North from Adelaide rounding the curve at Gallipoli Rd or crossing Mallala Rd.

places.name: Bolivar
places.desc: Very popular spot among photographers and gunzels, amazing view for trains going North, best for photography in the afternoon/evening when standing in the West, but can also work in the morning when standing in the East.

places.name: Gaol Loop
places.desc: Trains pass the old Adelaide Gaol parallel to the original Broad Gauge track (now disused). Also passes close to the Abandoned Gaol signal box and the Heritage Old Adelaide Gaol.

places.name: Long Plains (LPN).
places.desc:
Location: 77.3km by Rail from Mile End.
Length: 1900m.

places.name: Ambleside (AMB).
places.desc:
Location: 42.67km by Rail from Mile End.
Length: 1850m.

places.name: Adelaide Showgrounds
places.desc: Good spot for trains in both directions, additionally it is handy in low light conditions or night time as there are lights from the station.

places.name: Greenfields.
places.desc: Good views in both directions. In the morning photography is best from the Platform of Greenfields Station. In the afternoon photography is best from the walking trail on the Western side of the Railway Line.

places.name: Mile End Datum
places.desc: Marks "0km". Kilometrage increases in both directions from this point.

places.name: Bishop (BSP).
places.desc:
Location: 3.1km by Rail from Dry Creek Jct.
Length: 1500m. Named after long serving railwayman George Bishop. 

Bluescope Lysaght's Siding is located off of the Loop towards the former Wingfield Rd Level Crossing.

places.name: Mount Barker Junction.
places.desc: Mt Barker Junction is the start of the Steamranger Heritage Railway to Victor Harbor, however, the Mt Barker Jct - Mt Barker section is closed.

places.name: Belair (BEL).
places.desc:
Location: 21.5km by Rail from Mile End.
Length: 1543m.

places.name: Glenalta
places.desc: Great for trains heading uphill from Downer Avenue. Popular spot for SA train photographers, best used between 14:00 and 16:00 in Winter.

places.name: Berth 29, Port Adelaide.
places.desc:
Part of the larger Port Flat Yard owned by Aurizon.

Container services such as the Wirrida ore service (attached to AD/DA intermodals to Dry Creek then tripped to here) for the Prominent Hill Mine unload here. 
The Aurizon mineral sands train (1501S/5100S) from Broken Hill unloads here, as well as Qube's lead/zinc rasp train, also from Broken Hill.

places.name: Two Wells (TWO).
places.desc:
Location: Two Wells 44.8km by Rail from Mile End.
Length: 1817m
Engineers Siding located off of the Loop at the Southern End.

Photography at either Northern (Temby Rd) End, Middle (Sharpe Rd) Southern End (Gawler Rd).

places.name: Fosters Corner
places.desc:
Viewing spot.

It is also just around the corner from Belair Crossing Loop.

places.name: Gillman Yard (Port Flat) (PFL)
places.desc:
Multi User yard owned by Aurizon, now known as Gillman yard since late 2023.

Includes a container hardstand used for Aurizon's Intermodal services to Port Pirie, Melbourne, Perth and Darwin. Aurizon's 1501S/5100S mineral sands as well as occasional grain trains commence/terminate here and discharge nearby at Berth 29 and Viterra respectively. QUBE also visit the yard once weekly with the lead/zinc rasp train, also ex Broken Hill.

places.name: Henschke Street (Foamer Street)
places.desc:
Popular Spot for SA gunzels, useful for photographing any services coming from or going to Crystal Brook and beyond (Northbound).

Also useful for viewing most movements in and out of the Adelaide Metro Depot.

places.name: Mt Lofty
places.desc: The summit of the South line, where trains coming from both the East and the West reach the top and then descend downgrade under dynamic braking, popular spot for filming trains as they climb the grade, especially in the morning.

places.name: Top Tunnel
places.desc: Trains sound great coming in and going out of the tunnel. Access via Saddle Hill Road walking track.

places.name: Mile End (MED).
places.desc:
Location: 0.0km by Rail from Mile End and 3.4km by Rail from Adelaide Station.
Length: 1818m.
Engineers Siding located off of the Loop towards the Southern End.

places.name: Port Flat Triangle
places.desc: Used to turn locomotives as required.

places.name: Bolivar Loop (BOL)
places.desc:
Distance: 31.5km from Mile End
Length: 1880m. Also 250m Engineers siding at the down end.
Crossing loop. 
SCT's Penfield facility is accessed from this loop.

places.name: Gawler EMU Depot
places.desc: Stabling sidings for Adelaide Metro's EMU sets

places.name: SCT Penfield
places.desc: SCT's Penfield terminal, regular traffic includes the MP9/PM9, AG1 services as well as shuttle services between Port Germein and Penfield, Steel transfers to Wingfield, QUBE also pick up the SCT Wine train consist here on 4120/1421S (SCT also sometimes transfer it themselves, usually combining it with the steel transfers).

places.name: Dry Creek Triangle (DJN).
places.desc:
The Port Line diverges here to serve Pelican Point and Port Flat, as well as Lysaght's Siding in Wingfield and the Mobil Fuel depot at Birkenhead. 

Aurizon, Bowmans Rail, Pacific National & SCT also use the triangle to turn Locomotives.

places.name: Kilburn Railway Station
places.desc: Diamond crossover between the ARTC standard gauge line & Adelaide Metro Broad Gauge line. Good views into Islington freight terminal.

places.name: Hawthorn Pedestrian Crossing
places.desc: Amazing straight views in each direction, photo's of South bound trains work best when taken in the morning during Summer and North bounds also during the morning year rond.

places.name: FACT Pelican Point
places.desc: The QUBE Balco service from Bowmans, as well as the Wine train and some ore services load and unload here.

places.name: Islington
places.desc:
Great views of trains in both directions, particularly in the mornings. 

Northbound / from the Regency Road Bridge
Southbound / from the Pedestrian Crossing

places.name: RailFirst Asset Management Islington Workshop
places.desc:
RFAM's Adelaide Workshops. Locomotives and Rolling Stock are stored and maintained here. Locomotives owned by other operators are repaired/repainted here.

The workshops were originally built by the South Australian Railways.

places.name: Aldgate
places.desc: Beautiful maintained station with great views of trains coming up from Adelaide.

places.name: Grainflow Mallala
places.desc:
Distance: 60.2km from Mile End
GrainFlow Balloon loop, Served by Aurizon as 1431S/4132S.

places.name: Adelaide Metro Dry Creek Railcar Depot
places.desc: Heavy maintenance centre for Adelaide Metro's fleet of 4000, 3000 and 3100 series EMU/DMU trains.

places.name: Sleeps Hill Tunnel
places.desc: Great viewing spot from on top of the hills and around to see trains coming out of and going into the tunnel on both sides

places.name: Viterra Pelican Point
places.desc: Majority of SA's Grain services unload on this balloon loop.

places.name: Edinburgh Road
places.desc: Great spot for photographing trains coming out of Adelaide in the mornings

places.name: Adelaide Freight Terminal (AFT) (Islington).
places.desc: Pacific National's Adelaide Intermodal Terminal, MA/AM, MP/PM, AB/BA, AX/XA all depart from here.

places.name: Adelaide Parklands Terminal (APT/KWK)
places.desc: All Passenger Services operated by Journey Beyond Rail (JBRE) Depart and Arrive here, including AD8/DA8, AP8/PA8, AS8/SA8, AM8/MA8 & AT8/TA8.

places.name: Balhannah
places.desc:
Distance: 45.912km from Mile End.
Length: 694m.
Good spot for Down (Morning) and Up (Afternoon) trains. 

Crossing loop is rarely used due to its length, occasionally trains run through it just to clean the railhead but don't stop.

places.name: Belair Railcar Sidings
places.desc: 3000/3100 class DMUs are kept here for Belair line services

places.name: Dry Creek North Yard (DCN)
places.desc:
Multi user yard owned by Aurizon, hoppers and wagons are stabled here awaiting their next assignments.

Aurizon's four weekly (in each direction) Intermodal services between Melbourne and Perth also stage, shunt and add additional loading here.

places.name: Port River Bridge
places.desc:
View of trains crossing the bridge.

Services to see: Grain Trains, Light Engine Movements, the Mobil Fuel Train, and the Balco/Wine Train.

places.name: Onkaparinga Road/SEF overpass bridge view
places.desc: Bridge spot with a nice narrow straight for photos on UP trains and a nice view under the freeway for photos/videos on DOWN trains, from experience this spot is best used in the morning but can also be used at all times due to the fair amount of shade!

places.name: Wheel Lathe, Rollingstock Maintenance and Operations Centre, Dry Creek South.
places.desc:
Aurizon's Wheel Lathe and Rollingstock Maintenace Facility for the Bulk Central Division.

Rollingstock Maintenance occurs here, as well as various Operators bringing their Locomotives here to pass over the Wheel Lathe as required.

Train control for the Darwin & other Aurizon managed lines is also located in buildings adjacent to the sheds as well as the drivers depot.
